(Description)
Given the root of a binary tree, invert the tree, and return its root.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public TreeNode invertTree(TreeNode root) {
        if (root == null) {
            return null;
        }

        TreeNode temp = root.right;
        root.right = root.left;
        root.left = temp;

        invertTree(root.left);
        invertTree(root.right);
        
        return root;
    }
}

--- Approach ---
The main of this problem is changing left and right node at every nodes.
Therefore, Recursion was the key concept in this problem.
At every nodes, from root to leaves, invertTree changes root.right and root.left, under the recursion.
